1. CREATE A NEW TEMP_ENV LIST

ex:
Minishell>> temp=hola

this adds to the temp list, but not the original
t_env list. Test many posibilities

IDEA:
a. Create a new t_env *temp in data, and also run the expander in those

b. Every time we recieve an inmut, check for the grammar in order to
  add this var into the t_env *temp list.

ex:
Minishell>> export temp

a. This will fist check if this variables exists in the t_env *temp
  list before, to add it. If it doesnt exists, wors as normal and adds
  temp as the key and in that case with no value.

