4. The Exit Code Check: After killing cat with Ctrl-C, type echo $?. It must be 130. If killed with Ctrl-\, it must be 131.
5. The Command: echo "" "" ""

What they check for: It should print exactly two spaces. Many badly written parsers segfault on empty string tokens. 
6. The Command: export A="ls -l", then run $A.

What they check for: Word splitting. It should execute ls -l. Many parsers fail this and try to look for an executable literally named "ls -l".
7. Minishell>> ls > ""
minishell: : ambiguous redirect
Minishell>> exit
xiribar@c1r13s2:/goinfre/minishell$ ls > ""
bash: : No such file or directory
